Stacey Tadd (born 21 February 1989 in Bath, Somerset, England) is a British breaststroke swimmer.
Tadd was selected to represent Great Britain at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the 200 m breaststroke.Stacey's best international results, to the start of London 2012 Summer Olympics, came in the 2003 European Youth Olympic Festival where she won two gold medals and a bronze.
